UCISA Academic Administration
Documentation: All activities aimed at managing academic policies, regulations, scheduling and related customer feedback.

Name: UCISA Academic Advice Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure academic advice is provided for students, including insight, direction, and planning of their academic career.

Name: UCISA Academic Policy & Regulation Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to create, review, administer and revise Academic policies and regulations.

Name: UCISA Academic Skills Development
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure students are assisted with their academic skills development, including development of skills in research, use of library resources, academic writing, work planning and critical thinking.

Name: UCISA Academic Year Scheduling
Documentation: What the organisation does to schedule the curriculum across the academic year.

Name: UCISA Accommodation Allocation
Documentation: What the organisation does to allocate accommodation to students who have requested it, or to other people staying there when not occupied by students, and to enable an orderly occupation of accommodation upon arrival, and the management of room transfers and student withdrawals.

Name: UCISA Accommodation Departure & Turnaround Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to enable an orderly departure of residents at the end of their tenancy and ensure the accommodation is properly prepared for its next resident.

Name: UCISA Accommodation Facilities Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure accommodation is appropriately furnished and equipped, including repair and replacement of furnishings and equipment as needed.

Name: UCISA Accommodation Incident & Emergency Response
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure it is able to react and respond appropriately to emergencies and other serious incidents that occur in or affect student accommodation, including the ability to keep residents safely housed even during occurrences that mean standard accommodation is temporarily vacated.

Name: UCISA Accommodation Management
Documentation: All activities aimed at the provision of accommodation to students, and potentially other people when not occupied by students.

Name: UCISA Alumni Engagement
Documentation: All activities aimed at Alumni engagement ensuring the organisations alumni is fully involved in the life of the institution as valued supporters, advocates, and lifelong learners who contribute to, and benefit from, connections to each other and to the organisation.

Name: UCISA Alumni Event & Campaign Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the development and management of alumni related events and campaigns.

Name: UCISA Alumni Relationship Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the effective communication and interaction with past students of the organisation.

Name: UCISA Application Lifecycle Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to create and manage applications in support of organisational requirements.

Name: UCISA Art/Museum Collection Mgt
Documentation: What the Organisation does to manage, maintain and secure its art and museum collections, including acquisition, cataloguing and loans.

Name: UCISA Assessment Administration
Documentation: What the organisation does to administer the assessment of students, ensuring regulations, policies and processes are followed, and that there is a clear communications strategy so students are aware of the assessment regime and their responsibilities.

Name: UCISA Assessment Delivery
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that students are assessed against the learning outcomes of their curriculum proportionately and using the most appropriate assessment method.

Name: UCISA Assessment Marking & Feedback
Documentation: What the organisation does to mark, benchmark and moderate assessments, and provide feedback to students that facilitates their development as learners.

Name: UCISA Asset Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure a systematic process of deploying, operating, maintaining, upgrading, and disposing of assets cost-effectively.

Name: UCISA Benefactor Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure effective engagement with potential / actual benefactors. Benefactors may provide financial donations or other help.

Name: UCISA Benefits Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to identify, measure and evaluate the anticipated benefits associated with a given change initiative.

Name: UCISA Brand Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure its brand is perceived positively, presented consistently and segregated from its competition.

Name: UCISA Budget Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the analysis, organisation and oversight of costs and expenditures within the business. This will include adhering to strict internal protocols on income & expenditures.

Name: UCISA Business & Operational Reporting
Documentation: What the organisation does to understand requirements, source data, validate quality and publish reports – on any platform – to underpin its daily operations and support its tactical and strategic planning.

Name: UCISA Business Capability Management
Documentation: All activities aimed at understanding, prioritising, delivering and managing the capabilities needed to support the strategy(s) and vision.

Name: UCISA Business Continuity Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the development, testing, and maintenance of business continuity plans.

Name: UCISA Business Horizon Scanning
Documentation: What the organisation does to review developments within the sector and in the world at large to inform strategic development.

Name: UCISA Campaign Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to raise awareness of its courses and services through planning, execution, tracking and analysis of marketing campaigns.

Name: UCISA Campus Parking
Documentation: What the organisation does to provide the appropriate level of car parking availability.

Name: UCISA Campus Security
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the safety of the onsite community including monitoring and responding to unacceptable or criminal behaviour.

Name: UCISA Career & Employability Engagement Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to engage with prospective employers and to ensure students are provided with direction and careers advice in order to help them develop and realise their career ambitions and to maximise their employment prospects.

Name: UCISA Change Portfolio Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to govern and manage the entire institution change portfolio - including all programmes, projects and initiatives - their prioritisation and oversight.

Name: UCISA Child Care Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that there is suitable childcare advice and support available to staff and students. This may include childcare facilities, vouchers, etc.

Name: UCISA Collaborative Opportunity Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to investigate and support opportunities for research that involve relationships or partnerships with other organisations.

Name: UCISA Commercial Activity
Documentation: All capabilities required to ensure that the organisation is able to develop, deliver, support and administer commercial activity.

Name: UCISA Commercial Activity Exit Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure all relevant processes are in place to allow the organisation to cease specific commercial activities with the least harmful effect.

Name: UCISA Commercial Activity Issue Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that all issues effecting commercial activity are handled speedily and effectively, within legal parameters, with the specific aim of minimising business damage and adverse brand reputation.

Name: UCISA Commercial Activity Output Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the relevant processes are in place to deliver and communicate related time, quality, resource and risks associated to commercial outputs.

Name: UCISA Commercial Activity Reporting
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the effective reporting of commercial activity performance, good or bad, within the organisation.

Name: UCISA Commercial Contingency Planning
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure commercial activities can continue in the event of unplanned activities, such as supplier failure, emergency or disaster.

Name: UCISA Commercial Contract Performance Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the process of systematically and efficiently managing contract execution and analysis for the purpose of maximising financial and operational performance and minimising risk.

Name: UCISA Commercial Delivery
Documentation: All activities aimed at the successful fulfilment of the organisations commercial activity commitments.

Name: UCISA Commercial Engagement
Documentation: All activities aimed at managing the organisations relationship with commercial partners.

Name: UCISA Commercial Market Analysis
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that it has in place effective processes for the gathering of information about past, current and future states of the commercial marketplace in which it is looking to operate.

Name: UCISA Commercial Monitoring
Documentation: All activities aimed at scrutinising the effectiveness and performance of all commercial endeavours within the organisation.

Name: UCISA Commercial Opportunity Assessment
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that it has the relevant measures in place to compare and evaluate commercial opportunities.

Name: UCISA Commercial Opportunity Identification
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that it can identify potential new commercial opportunities across all sectors in which it is looking to operate.

Name: UCISA Commercial Partner Engagement
Documentation: What the organisation does to initially identify, engage with, contract, administer and maintain commercial partners.

Name: UCISA Commercial Partner Integration & Transition
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage assimilation and change in the relationship with commercial partners.

Name: UCISA Commercial Sourcing
Documentation: All activities aimed at ensuring that the organisation can effectively identify and assess commercial opportunities.

Name: UCISA Commercial Tenancy
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage external tenants.

Name: UCISA Commercialise Research Outcomes
Documentation: What the organisation does to plan and realise the commercial potential of its research outcomes, including contract and intellectual property management.

Name: UCISA Complaint & Compliment Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to receive, manage and respond to any complaints or compliments related to any aspect of its business.

Name: UCISA Compliance Monitoring & Reporting
Documentation: What the organisation does to monitor and report on compliance with institutional Policies and Standards.

Name: UCISA Contract Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that all contracts are effectively managed within required frameworks.

Name: UCISA Copyright Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to secure data under copyright, including identification, assessment, monitoring and intervention in the case of breach, and ensuring appropriate use of data copyrighted by other persons or organisations.

Name: UCISA Corporate Governance
Documentation: All activities aimed at ensuring compliance with external regulations and internal policies, including management of risk.

Name: UCISA Corporate Performance Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to set, measure and assess targets and metrics for key corporate objectives.

Name: UCISA Curriculum & Resource Development
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that the relevant resources are available to deliver the curriculum components e.g. learning spaces, books etc.

Name: UCISA Curriculum Change Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure educators and administrators collaborate on the review and refinement of curriculum components to achieve desired student outcomes.

Name: UCISA Curriculum Design
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure educators and administrators collaborate on the creation, development, design, approval and release of new curriculum components to achieve desired student outcomes.

Name: UCISA Curriculum Management
Documentation: All activities aimed at educators and administrators collaborating on the creation, development, design, review, approval, assessment, and refinement of curriculum content to achieve desired student outcomes.

Name: UCISA Curriculum Performance Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to develop and support the organisation's quality assurance framework e.g. Academic Committees, Annual programme monitoring, Periodic programme review, Course Approval & modifications etc.

Name: UCISA Curriculum Retirement Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure educators and administrators withdraw & retire curriculum components.

Name: UCISA Digital Communication Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to facilitate communications between stakeholders over digital channels and ensure that new channels are identified and adopted as required.

Name: UCISA Disability Support Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure students who disclose a disability or require additional support for their academic studies receive  the support  and advice they need to achieve their full potential.

Name: UCISA Dispute Resolution
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage and resolve legal and legislative disputes.

Name: UCISA Domestic Student Recruitment
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the effective recruitment of prospective domestic students.

Name: UCISA Employee Performance Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure expectations of employee performance are set, and individual objectives are established and assessed. This includes ensuring measures can be put in place to manage and improve unacceptable performance.

Name: UCISA Employee Support
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure its employees are provided with assistance, advice and guidance about personal and employment matters that might affect health, wellbeing or performance.

Name: UCISA Enabling Capabilities
Documentation: All capabilities required to ensure that the organisation is able to provide general financial, adminstrative, physical and technical support to the core activities of Strategy & Governance, Teaching & Learning, Research and Commercial Activity.

Name: UCISA End User Computing
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the availability of end user devices and/or access by end user devices.

Name: UCISA Enrolment Status Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the change of students' official statuses as members of the organisation in response to requests or changes in situation, and in accordance with the relevant regulations. This includes the abilities to interrupt/suspend studies for a period, withdraw from units of study, programmes of study and/or the organisation, and to transfer between units/modules of study.

Name: UCISA Enterprise Architecture
Documentation: What the organisation does to develop and maintain architectural deliverables to support effective business decision making.

Name: UCISA Enterprise Content Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to acquire, maintain and manage content across both digital and physical platforms.

Name: UCISA Environmental Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage environmental services.

Name: UCISA Estate Development & Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that its estate is effectively developed and managed to meet both current and future requirements.

Name: UCISA Event Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure large scale events, such as open days, conferences and high-profile public lectures, are planned, coordinated and operated satisfactorily.

Name: UCISA Expenditure Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the effective payment of creditors, suppliers and customers.

Name: UCISA Facilities & Property Management
Documentation: All activities aimed at ensuring that organisational facilities and properties are fit for purpose, future-proofed and maintained to the appropriate standards, including security and health and safety.

Name: UCISA Finance Management
Documentation: All activities aimed at the efficient and effective management of money (funds) in such a manner as to allow the organisation to accomplish its objectives.

Name: UCISA Financial Advisory
Documentation: What the organisation does to offer specialist financial advice.

Name: UCISA Financial Reporting
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the accurate and secure preparation, production and publication of financial information for both internal & external consumption.

Name: UCISA Food & Retail Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage the provision of food and retail outlets and associated services on campus and at associated locations. This includes payment services, e-commerce, stock management and logistics.

Name: UCISA Government Relationship Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure it effectively manages and maintains its ties with government bodies.

Name: UCISA Government, Public & Stakeholder Relationships
Documentation: All activities aimed at ensuring a continuous level of engagement is maintained between the organisation and its customers, stakeholders & other interested parties.

Name: UCISA Graduation Eligibility Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that the administrative and financial (debt) affairs of students are in order, and those eligible to graduate are determined. This does not include academic results or exam/review boards.

Name: UCISA Graduation Event Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to stage the ceremony at which degrees are formally and publicly conferred by the organisation to eligible graduands. This includes the abilities to make the necessary arrangements for the event(s), and the carrying out of the graduation ceremony itself along with other associated events.

Name: UCISA Graduation Record Certificate Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure accurate records, relating to the formal qualifications awarded to students, are produced and maintained. This includes degree award certificates, Diploma Supplements and other associated certificates and records, and the ability to provide records and certificates as required.

Name: UCISA Health & Safety
Documentation: What the organisation does to provide an environment conducive to the health and safety of the entire onsite community.

Name: UCISA Health Care Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to make sure that efficient and effective health care services are available. It will ensure that students know how to access these services, especially students not from the UK.

Name: UCISA High Performance Computing
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure access to HPC services.

Name: UCISA Housing Advice
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure students have access to the support and advice required to enable them to secure accommodation that suits their needs and budget, whether that be organisation halls or private accommodation.

Name: UCISA Human Resource Management
Documentation: All activities aimed at the management and organisation of staff and their contribution to the institution.

Name: UCISA ICT Service Support
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the delivery of customer focused ICT service support.

Name: UCISA Identity & Access Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage data on IT systems and applications about users. Managed data includes user objects, identity attributes, security entitlements and authentication factors.

Name: UCISA Income Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the effective invoicing, collection and allocation of monies into the organisation, including debt management.

Name: UCISA Industry Relationship Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure it effectively establishes, develops and nurtures a network of mutually beneficial industry relationships.

Name: UCISA Information & Communication Technology Mgt
Documentation: All activities aimed at the efficient and effective development, delivery and management of ICT resources and access to those resources.

Name: UCISA Information & Data Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage institutional data, including planning for sourcing and storage, ensuring data is fit for purpose including sourcing and maintenance of data necessary to support the organisations business (may include geospatial, social, economic, demographic data).

Name: UCISA Information & Data Security Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to assess, mark, monitor, manage and maintain information security,  and intervene/escalate in the event of breach of the Information Security policy. This will include complying with regulation, legislation and internal risk management.

Name: UCISA Information Analytics
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the application of appropriate analytical techniques, including support for advanced analytics and their application to large data sets, providing the organisation with greater insight into their data.

Name: UCISA Information Collection Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to understand, acquire, store archive and delete/sunset information which requires collection, validation, quality checking, use and re-use.

Name: UCISA Information Management
Documentation: All activities aimed at acquiring, storing, exploiting, archiving and deleting information in the organisation. Information under management includes structured and unstructured data as defined as in scope by the data governance, data security and data management policies.

Name: UCISA Information Search & Discovery
Documentation: What the organisation does to locate, index, catalogue and publish information for both internal and external use. This may include data not held by the organisation.

Name: UCISA Infrastructure Lifecycle Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to create and manage infrastructure in support of organisational requirements.

Name: UCISA Insurance Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the relevant provisions are in place to provide a means of protection from financial loss.

Name: UCISA Internal Audit & Reporting
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage and undertake the internal audit and compliance program.

Name: UCISA Internal Communications
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that all constituent parts can communicate effectively using appropriate means across all aspects of the business.

Name: UCISA Internal Stakeholder Relationship Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure it facilitates, develops and maintains internal stakeholder engagement & dialogue.

Name: UCISA International Student Recruitment
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the effective recruitment of prospective international students to agreed targets.

Name: UCISA Knowledge Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to acquire, enrich, share, store, publish and enhance the expertise across the whole organisation.

Name: UCISA Legal & Legislative Compliance
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure compliance with all appropriate legal and legislative requirements.

Name: UCISA Legal Advisory
Documentation: What the organisation does to provide effective legal advisory services to its community.

Name: UCISA Legal Services
Documentation: All activities aimed at ensuring the availability of effective legal services.

Name: UCISA Library Collection Access Mgt
Documentation: What the Organisation does to manage loaning and access to library collections and resources both physical and electronic, by students, staff and the wider community, in line with license and subscription agreements.

Name: UCISA Library Collection Resource Mgt
Documentation: What the Organisation does to manage the its library collections and resources, including acquisition, invoicing and cataloguing, covering both physical and electronic assets.

Name: UCISA Library Management
Documentation: All activities related to the management of library resources and access to those resources. This does not include the physical library environment.

Name: UCISA Library Membership Mgt
Documentation: What the Organisation does to manage membership of the library, covering students, staff and the wider community.

Name: UCISA Mail Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the distribution of mail both internally and externally.

Name: UCISA Manage Research Relationships
Documentation: What the organisation does to plan, manage and cultivate its research relationships with other organisations, including the management of partner relationships and for knowledge exchange relationships.

Name: UCISA Market Research
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure information is gathered, analysed, understood and disseminated about the market(s) in which it operates, or may operate in future. This includes understanding the needs and preferences of those the organisation aims to serve, and the viability of the services it offers now or plans to offer.

Name: UCISA Marketing Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure it puts into practice the appropriate techniques, methods and structures in order to market the organisation.

Name: UCISA Media Relations Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure it promotes and enhances its profile and reputation regionally, nationally and internationally. Through the publicising of research and expertise, achievements and successes to a range of media and networks, while also responding to direct enquires from the press, maximising positive coverage in the media.

Name: UCISA Merchandising
Documentation: What the organisation does to promote the sale of products in a retail setting.

Name: UCISA Module Selection Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that students are fully enrolled on the necessary modules for their programme of study, including pre-enrolment where appropriate and provision of full information to enable informed module choice.

Name: UCISA Non Presence Based Teaching
Documentation: What the organisation does to provide teaching activities via online and digital channels that enable learning for students not physically located with the teaching content provider.

Name: UCISA Non-Academic Achievement Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the recognition and recording of achievements made by students at organisation, other than formal academic awards. This includes abilities to produce HEARs (Higher Education Achievement Reports), recognise outstanding extra-curricular activities and voluntary work, and to bestow intuition-specific prizes.

Name: UCISA Non-Commercial Research Impact Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to plan and realise the non-commercial potential of its research outcomes, including for social good.

Name: UCISA Occupational Health
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the physical and mental wellbeing of its employees in the workplace.

Name: UCISA Offer, Acceptance & Quota Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure student offers are distributed, acceptances are processed and quotas are managed, including confirmation activities.

Name: UCISA Organisational Design
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that its structures are optimised to support operational excellence and delivery of strategic objectives.

Name: UCISA Other Tertiary Institution Relationship Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to identify key peer tertiary institutions, and manage and maintain these relationships.

Name: UCISA Personal Learning Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure students requiring additional support receive an individual personal learning plan to help them achieve their short and long term goals.

Name: UCISA Personal Tutor Provision
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure delivery of personal tutoring to students to help them make a successful transition into H.E. and aid their academic progression and achievement, including provision of academic and personal support and guidance, and signposting to other support services.

Name: UCISA PGR Student Skills Development
Documentation: What the organisation does to develop its postgraduate research students so as to equip them with the necessary skills to undertake, defend and publish their research.

Name: UCISA PGR Supervisor Development
Documentation: What the organisation does to develop the supervisory and support skills of those staff who supervise postgraduate research students.

Name: UCISA Policy & Regulation Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to develop, manage, maintain and enforce corporate polices, regulations and standards in line with internal and external requirements.

Name: UCISA Presence Based Teaching
Documentation: What the organisation does to provide face to face teaching activities that enable learning and associated resources, to students physically located with the teaching content provider.

Name: UCISA Printing Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to provide print services to students and staff, including provision of accounts for payment when required and printing in custom sizes and formats.

Name: UCISA Private Sector Housing Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to provide tools and services to help students find private accommodation to rent whilst they are at the organisation.

Name: UCISA Procurement & Purchasing Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the effective sourcing, purchasing and supply of the goods and services that enable the organisation to operate.

Name: UCISA Professional Accreditation
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the academic curriculum is accredited by a professional authority.

Name: UCISA Professional Learning (Staff)
Documentation: What the organisation does to support the enhancement of the student learning experience through initial and continuing professional development of Academic staff.

Name: UCISA Programme & Project Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure effective management of programmes and projects.

Name: UCISA Programme Enrolment
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that students are fully enrolled on their chosen programme of study, including provisional enrolment, confirmation, and capture of all necessary personal details.

Name: UCISA Programme Transfer Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure a student's enrolment on one programme can be ceased, and enrolment onto an alternative programme performed, within limitations that may be imposed in terms of time, academic requirements, fees or other administrative reasons.

Name: UCISA Promotions Management
Documentation: All activities aimed at the promotion of the institution to prospective and current students, businesses and the general public.

Name: UCISA Property Maintenance
Documentation: What the organisation does to maintain its estate to appropriate and acceptable levels.

Name: UCISA Prospective Student Engagement
Documentation: What the organisation does to engage with, and promote the organisation to, prospective students.

Name: UCISA Public Relationship Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure it establishes and maintains mutually beneficial relationships between the organisation and the public, through a programme of corporate, annual and one off external-facing events, as well as a programme of collaborative and community-focussed events.

Name: UCISA Quality Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to assess service quality, and determine and monitor quality improvement activities.

Name: UCISA Records Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that that records are managed in accordance with internal and external requirements / regulations / law.

Name: UCISA Religious Support
Documentation: What the organisation does to support the religious and spiritual needs of staff and students, including the provision of care services, events and facilities.

Name: UCISA Remuneration & Entitlements Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure it rewards its staff appropriately in terms of pay, pension and other benefits.

Name: UCISA Research
Documentation: All capabilities required to ensure that the organisation is able to develop, deliver, support and administer research.

Name: UCISA Research Administration
Documentation: All activities aimed at administering and supporting the organisation's research environment.

Name: UCISA Research Compliance Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage and ensure compliance with research rules and regulations, including ethics.

Name: UCISA Research Dataset Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to store, share, use and re-use datasets produced from research projects, including dataset management planning and curation of datasets beyond the lifetime of individual projects.

Name: UCISA Research Delivery
Documentation: All activities aimed at undertaking and delivering the research itself.

Name: UCISA Research Funding
Documentation: All activities aimed at obtaining and managing funds to undertake research projects.

Name: UCISA Research Funding Identification
Documentation: What the organisation does to identify and secure sources of funding necessary to undertake research projects, including grant proposal and bid preparation.

Name: UCISA Research Funds Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to properly and effectively manage research funds throughout research projects, once secured.

Name: UCISA Research Impact
Documentation: All activities aimed at maximising and promoting the impacts of research undertaken at the organisation.

Name: UCISA Research Improvement
Documentation: All activities aimed at the continuous improvement of research quality and performance.

Name: UCISA Research Infrastructure Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage its specialist research infrastructure.

Name: UCISA Research Opportunity & Planning
Documentation: All activities aimed at determining and defining the research programmes and projects that will be undertaken at the organisation.

Name: UCISA Research Opportunity Analysis
Documentation: What the organisation does to identify and analyse opportunities and ideas for research programmes and projects.

Name: UCISA Research Output Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage the outputs that are produced from research projects, including curation of those outputs beyond the lifetime of individual projects.

Name: UCISA Research Output Reporting
Documentation: What the organisation does to develop and produce reports on research outputs, including those necessary to meet the requirements of funding bodies.

Name: UCISA Research Prioritisation
Documentation: What the organisation does to determine the priority of potential research programmes and projects.

Name: UCISA Research Production
Documentation: What the organisation does to produce research. This is the execution of the research project.

Name: UCISA Research Programme Development
Documentation: What the organisation does to develop its programme of research, including the identification of high-level research goals and themes.

Name: UCISA Research Programme Performance Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to review and improve the performance of its research programme.

Name: UCISA Research Publication Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to publish and promote research findings, and holistically manage its publication collections to maximise impact.

Name: UCISA Research Publications
Documentation: All activities aimed at publishing research findings and reporting outputs.

Name: UCISA Research Quality Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to review and improve the quality of its research activities.

Name: UCISA Research Training
Documentation: All activities aimed at training and developing the organisation's researchers, including both staff and post-graduate research students.

Name: UCISA Researcher Performance Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to assess researcher performance and undertake performance improvement activities.

Name: UCISA Researcher Training & Development
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure researchers know what is expected of them and how that contributes to the wider objectives of the organisation. Ensuring researchers are fully equipped, from a skills perspective, to deliver impactful research projects.

Name: UCISA Risk Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to assess corporate risk, and to identify and monitor risk mitigation activities.

Name: UCISA Scholarship & Bursary Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure scholarships and bursaries are set, assessed, managed and awarded.

Name: UCISA Space Utilisation
Documentation: What the organisation does to maximise the utilisation of available space.

Name: UCISA Sport & Recreation Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to provide facilities for sport and other recreational activities to staff, students and the wider community where appropriate.

Name: UCISA Staff Absence Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the absence of employees is managed, recorded, authorised and followed up appropriately, along with ensuring work is adequately covered by other staff. This includes annual, sick, and other authorised leave, and unauthorised absence.

Name: UCISA Staff Engagement
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure its employees are motivated to contribute to the organisation's success and committed to the organisation’s goals and values.

Name: UCISA Staff Record & Details Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to maintain accurate information about employees, including contact, address and biographical details, contract management and document management. This includes appropriate record retention and disposal management.

Name: UCISA Staff Recruitment
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the best candidates are recruited to vacant posts, including identification of job requirements, attraction and selection of candidates, hiring and induction.

Name: UCISA Strategic Plan Development
Documentation: What the organisation does to develop, maintain and review strategic plans in support of its vision, mission and strategy.

Name: UCISA Strategic Plan Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to develop, maintain and review strategic plans in support of its vision, mission and strategy.

Name: UCISA Strategic Reporting
Documentation: What the organisation does to report on progress towards delivery of strategic plans and objectives.

Name: UCISA Strategic Vision Development
Documentation: What the organisation does to develop and maintain a coherent vision for the future.

Name: UCISA Strategy & Governance
Documentation: All capabilities required to ensure that the organisation is able to develop and maintain its strategic direction, manage continuous improvement, grow and share knowledge and best practice, and comply with external requirements.

Name: UCISA Strategy Management
Documentation: All activities aimed at ensuring that the organisation has a coherent, integrated and sustainable vision, mission and strategy.

Name: UCISA Student Administration
Documentation: All activities aimed at maintaining accurate records of students and their administrative and academic statuses during their time at organisation, and managing the change of records and statuses.

Name: UCISA Student Admission Management
Documentation: All activities aimed at managing student applications, placement offers and quotas.

Name: UCISA Student Application Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure student applications are assessed/evaluated, including assessment of prior learning, scheduling interviews and clearing activities.

Name: UCISA Student Assessment
Documentation: All activities aimed at assessing whether a student has achieved the learning outcomes of the curriculum.

Name: UCISA Student Attraction & Recruitment
Documentation: All activities aimed at planning and delivering campaigns and events that aim to recruit and convert undergraduate and postgraduate students to the organisation.

Name: UCISA Student Completion & Graduation
Documentation: All activities aimed at conferring degrees (and other awards) to students who have qualified appropriately and hence become graduates.

Name: UCISA Student Engagement & Retention
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure students are pro-actively engaged in the learning process and want to continue their studies at the organisation.

Name: UCISA Student Enrolment
Documentation: All activities aimed at ensuring that students are fully enrolled at the programme and module level and inducted into the organisation community.

Name: UCISA Student Exceptional Factors Misconduct / Appeal Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure it can receive and process student submissions relating to mitigating circumstances, investigate and act in response to student misconduct, or allegations thereof, and handle subsequent formal challenges to those findings or actions. This includes ensuring the appropriate formal frameworks are in place for dealing with such situations. The term 'misconduct' can relate to academic offences, administrative discrepancies or behavioural conduct.

Name: UCISA Student Financial Administration
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure that all aspects of student finance are effectively managed, including fee setting and collection and debtor management.

Name: UCISA Student Financial Advice
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure students receive the help they need to manage their finances, including providing advice and guidance on financial matters and providing access to hardships funds if required.

Name: UCISA Student Health & Wellbeing
Documentation: What the organisation does to assist students with their health and wellbeing, including the provision of student wellbeing advice, mental health advice and counselling.

Name: UCISA Student Induction Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to introduce the student to the organisation and its communities, including activities which are intended to support students in making key transitions throughout their programme of study and/or life.

Name: UCISA Student Mobility
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure students can study and enrol at different universities, either as part of their award at the originating organisation or as a permanent transfer to the other organisation, and, vice-versa, the ability to accept students from other universities in the same fashion.

Name: UCISA Student Placement Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to source, allocate and manage the placement of students in learning and professional practice environments external to the organisation as part of the curriculum.

Name: UCISA Student Record & Details Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to maintain accurate information about students, including contact, address and biographical details, and document management. This includes appropriate record retention and disposal management.

Name: UCISA Student Recruitment Agent Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the effective management of external agents involved in the recruitment of students.

Name: UCISA Student Results Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage the gathering, aggregation and assignment of a student's results from a variety of assessment methods (including coursework, examinations and placements) as part of their curriculum and in accordance with academic regulations to provide assessment outcomes (e.g. progression and award).

Name: UCISA Student Support & Wellbeing Management
Documentation: All activities aimed at ensuring students receive adequate support and advice throughout their time at organisation.

Name: UCISA Supplier Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to plan and manage the relationships with third party suppliers of goods and services to maximise benefits.

Name: UCISA Supporting Services
Documentation: All activities that provide additional support to staff and students on and off campus to ensure a comprehensive range of services.

Name: UCISA Talent Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure succession planning, assessment, development and high-potential management of people particularly valuable to the organisation.

Name: UCISA Taxation Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the relevant strategy and procedures are in place to safeguard the organisation against its taxation risks and liabilities.

Name: UCISA Teaching & Learning
Documentation: All capabilities required to ensure that the organisation is able to develop, deliver, support and administer teaching and learning and the student experience.

Name: UCISA Teaching & Learning Content Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to provide resources in a wide range of formats to support learning and teaching in the organisation. This includes physical and digital resources such as the VLE and lecture capture, access to specialised space, library and other physical and digital services.

Name: UCISA Teaching & Learning Delivery
Documentation: All activities aimed at delivering a learning experience to students of the organisation and enabling them to engage with learning in the subjects as described in the curriculum. This includes the delivery of teaching activities as well as other activities that support a meaningful learning environment.

Name: UCISA Timetabling Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage the creation, revision and communication of the timing and location of curriculum events, including lectures, seminars, examinations and all similar/related activities.

Name: UCISA Training & Development
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure the acquisition of new, or enhancement of existing, knowledge and skills by its employees in order to provide the desired level of performance.

Name: UCISA Treasury Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure ongoing liquidity and mitigation of operational, financial and reputational risk through sound financial planning.

Name: UCISA Vehicle Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage its internal vehicle fleet.

Name: UCISA Venue Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to manage the provision and booking of venues, including the associated facilities, both internally and to external customers. This excludes event management.

Name: UCISA Wand Mgt
Documentation: What your wand does to choose you.

Name: UCISA Workforce Planning
Documentation: What the organisation does to forecast, recommend and report workforce requirements and performance, including structuring, based on the strategic objectives of the institution.

Name: UCISA Workforce Relations Mgt
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure a positive work environment, focus on individual and collective relationships, including unions, resolve workplace issues through intervention when necessary.

Name: UCISA Workforce Reporting
Documentation: What the organisation does to ensure it provides internal and external (including statutory) operational and strategic information about its workforce to those who need it.
